      ## Exercise 1: Installing and running Rails

  %section
    :markdown
      ## Goal
      * __browser__: http://localhost:3000
      * __error__: Internet Explorer cannot display the webpage

  %section
    :markdown
      ## Step 1: Rails installer

      On Windows, download Rails installer (Ruby 1.9) from [http://
      railsinstaller.org](http://
      railsinstaller.org) and install. You will be asked to enter your name
      and email.

  %section
    :markdown
      ## Step 2: Create Rails application

          cmd > rails new trips-app
          cmd > cd trips-app
          cmd > rails server

    %aside.notes
      :markdown
        * `bundle install` may take awhile to finish.
        * You may have to
          - make Windows firewall allow Ruby to access private network.
          - turn intranet settings in IE9.

